Privacy Policy
At Empresa Municipal de Transportes de València, hereinafter EMT, we undertake to protect privacy and the use personal data correctly. EMT complies with the requirements of Law 34/2002, of 11 July, on Information Society Services and Electronic Commerce.
Specifically, EMT complies with current regulations on the protection of personal data, in particular, the General Data Protection Regulation, GDPR (Regulation (EU) 2016/679 of the European Parliament and Council of 27 April 2016) and Organic Law 3/2018 of 5 December on the protection of natural persons with regard to the processing of personal data, the free movement of such data within the European Union and the guarantee of digital rights.
The data collected from each data subject for all processing shall be adequate, relevant and not excessive, the minimum necessary, in relation to the corresponding purposes for each case. The data subject may exercise the right of access, rectification, deletion (right to be forgotten), opposition to a specific type of processing, limitation or portability of their personal data. The data collected shall be kept for the strictly necessary period of time for any processing and shall be safeguarded with sufficient security measures (anonymised). Regardless of the legal basis that legitimises the processing of your personal data, EMT shall comply with the duty of confidentiality, even once the relationship has ended. In the event that EMT entrusts the processing to a third entity, EMT as data controller shall, in turn, select the entity which guarantees compliance with the General Data Protection Regulation.
EMT reserves the right to modify or adapt this Privacy Policy at any time. As such, we recommend that you check it each time you access the website
https://www.emtvalencia.es
.
The data subject shall be informed, prior to the collection of their data, of the general provisions regulated in this policy in accordance with the following aspects:
Who is responsible for processing your personal data?
What are your personal data processed for?
What is the legal basis that legitimises the processing of your personal data?
How long do we keep your personal data for?
Who can be a transferee or recipient of your personal data?
What are your rights in data protection and how can they be exercised?
Regulations governing the use of cookies in
www.emtvalencia.es
Privacy policy for Mobile Applications
1. Who is responsible for processing your personal data?
The data collected, or provided voluntarily, either by browsing the website, as well as all those you can provide in the contact forms, via email or telephone, shall be collected and processed by the processing controller, whose details are indicated below:
